The method is designed to be budget efficient, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also mentions using standard aggregation methods, which could be related to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with datasets with both categorical and continuous labels, which could be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
